The Herald Ellina Mhlanga Senior Sports Reporter TEAM Zimbabwe to the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games was officially unveiled today with five athletes set to represent the country in Japan. Zimbabwe will be sending a delegation of 18 people – five athletes and 15 officials. Donata Katai and Peter Wetzlar will represent the country in swimming. Athletics will field Ngoni Makusha. Vincent Scott and Peter Purcell-Gilpin will compete in golf and rowing respectively. The unveiling was done online. The Games are due to take place from July 23 to August 8. Minister of Youth, Sport, Arts and Recreation Kirsty Coventry congratulated the athletes and said it has not been easy qualifying for these Games taking into account the challenges posed by the Covid-19 pandemic. Team Zimbabwe Aquatics – Swimming Athletes: Donata Katai, Peter Wetzlar Coach: Lindsy Tudor-Cole Athletics Athlete: Ngoni Makusha Coach: Lisimati Phakamile Rowing Athlete: Peter Purcell-Gilpin Coach: James Alexander Stephenson Golf Athlete: Scott Vincent Coach/ Team Leader: Mufaro Chivonivoni Chef de Mission: Fredreck Ndlovu Team Admin: Memory Pakati Physiotherapist and Covid-19 Liaison Officer: Abigail Mnikwa ZOC President: Thabani Gonye ZOC Chef executive: Stephen Mudawarima Government Delegation Sports and Recreation Commission chairman Gerald Mlotshwa, PA to the Minister Tariro Kadzirange, Chairman Portfolio Committee Mathias Tongofa.